.TH "kvm_get_badinstrp" 9 "kvm_get_badinstrp" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kvm_get_badinstrp \- Get bad prior instruction encoding.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" kvm_get_badinstrp
.BI "(u32 *opc "  ","
.BI "struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu "  ","
.BI "u32 *out "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "opc" 12
Guest pointer to prior faulting instruction.
.IP "vcpu" 12
KVM VCPU information.
.IP "out" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Gets the instruction encoding of the prior faulting instruction (the branch
containing the delay slot which faulted), using the saved BadInstrP register
value if it exists, otherwise falling back to reading guest memory at \fIopc\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
The instruction encoding of the prior faulting instruction.
